Also, it was skimpy on the meat in the crust, and could use a little bit more filling (mung beans and sprouts), and the dipping sauce was way too salty so you couldn't dip the Banh Xeo in the sauce too much.
The staff was professional, helpful, and friendly.
I'd come back again.

